# baselines/python/

This directory is the Python-language baseline partition (v0.5.0+).

**Per Decision D1=B** (`docs/LANGUAGE-AGNOSTIC-DECISIONS.md`): per-language
baseline files live in `baselines/<lang>/` subdirectories. The contract
`scope: per-language, language: python` is stamped on each JSON file as it
materializes.

## Files that will land here on first Python pilot run (Phase B)

| File | Owner agent | Materializes when |
|---|---|---|
| `performance-baselines.json` | sdk-benchmark-devil | First Phase 3 T5 bench wave |
| `coverage-baselines.json` | sdk-testing-lead | First Phase 3 T2 coverage wave |
| `output-shape-history.jsonl` | learning-engine | First feedback phase append |
| `devil-verdict-history.jsonl` | learning-engine | First feedback phase append |
| `do-not-regenerate-hashes.json` | sdk-marker-scanner | First impl phase if any `[do-not-regenerate]` marker exists |
| `stable-signatures.json` | sdk-marker-scanner | First impl phase if any `[stable-since:]` marker exists |
| `regression-report-<run-id>.md` | baseline-manager | First Phase 3 regression event (if any) |

## Why this dir exists empty in Phase A

The `python.json` manifest declares ownership of these paths in its
`baselines.owns_per_language_paths` array. Declaration before
materialization is fine — `baseline-manager` and friends create the files
on first write. The empty dir + this README hold the partition slot so
that `git`-tracked structure is honest about the v0.5.0 scope.

This file (`.gitkeep`) is intentionally a markdown-flavored placeholder
rather than a zero-byte file so a future reader gets context.
